title: YouTube down in parts of Europe – reports — RT News
text:
YouTube down in parts of Europe – reports Published time: 21 Feb, 2017 18:53 Edited time: 21 Feb, 2017 19:04 Get short URL © Dado Ruvic / Reuters Popular video-sharing website YouTube is down for many users across parts of Europe, according to online outage reports. Trends Viral 
Disruption to the website is being felt in areas including the UK, France and Germany, reports Down Detector. — Jenn (@MajesticJune) 21 February 2017 
An error message has appeared on the YouTube site accompanied by a cartoon monkey with a hammer. 
“Sorry, something went wrong. A team of highly trained monkeys has been dispatched to deal with this situation. If you see them, send them this information as text (screenshots frighten them),” the message reads, alongside a paragraph of code. 
Youtube has yet to comment on the reasons for the outage. The blackout has seen many users react with messages of frustration online. Others, meanwhile, poked fun at the sudden service failure. 
Earlier this month, the video-sharing site reported issues with editing clips. This is now fixed! Thanks for your patience and happy editing. https://t.co/dc8kKY4PYU
